e = \lim\limits_{n \rightarrow \infty} \left(1+\frac{1}{n}\right)^n
 \left( 1 + \frac{1}{n} \right)^n = \sum_{j=0}^{n} \binom{n}{j}\frac{1}{n^j} = \sum_{j=0}^{n} \frac{1}{j!}\prod_{k=1}^{j} \left( 1 - \frac{k-1}{n} \right) 
